# Personal Preferences

## Responses

- Keep your responses as short as possible they should only contain required information no fluff or unrelated wording.
- When writting documents keep the language concise do not dump a massive document step through it piece by piece.
- Never use weird unicode symbol variants e.g. emdashes, quotes, emojis, arrows. Prefer normal english ascii symbols.
  - Prefer: `-` `"` `'` `_` `->`

## Typescript

- Never use `any` unless absolutely required. Less strict in unit tests about this.

## Markdown

- Prefer headings over tables when the table would only have 2 columns

## Commands

- Dont run the dev server or any command that are probably already running as a watcher just assume it is.
- Prefer check/linting commands e.g. `npm run lint` etc
